  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "For a 2nd alto looking for great karaoke songs, you'll want tracks that typically sit in a lower vocal range but still allow for expressive singing. Here are some suggestions across various genres that are generally suitable for a 2nd alto voice:\n\n### Pop\n1. **\"Someone Like You\" - Adele**\n2. **\"Valerie\" - Amy Winehouse**\n3. **\"I Will Survive\" - Gloria Gaynor**\n4. **\"Killing Me Softly\" - Roberta Flack / Fugees**\n5. **\"Landslide\" - Fleetwood Mac**\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **\"Ain't No Mountain High Enough\" - Marvin Gaye & Tammi Terrell**\n2. **\"Natural Woman\" - Aretha Franklin**\n3. **\"Respect\" - Aretha Franklin**\n4. **\"Back to Black\" - Amy Winehouse**\n5. **\"Chain of Fools\" - Aretha Franklin**\n\n### Classic Rock\n1. **\"Dreams\" - Fleetwood Mac**\n2. **\"Babe I'm Gonna Leave You\" - Led Zeppelin**\n3. **\"Light My Fire\" - The Doors**\n4. **\"Brown Eyed Girl\" - Van Morrison**\n5. **\"Take it Easy\" - Eagles**\n\n### Contemporary Ballads\n1. **\"Fix You\" - Coldplay**\n2. **\"All of Me\" - John Legend**\n3. **\"The A Team\" - Ed Sheeran**\n4. **\"Say You Won't Let Go\" - James Arthur**\n5. **\"Shallow\" - Lady Gaga & Bradley Cooper (second parts can suit 2nd altos)**\n\n### Musical Theatre\n1. **\"Somewhere\" - West Side Story**\n2. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\" - Les Mis\u00e9rables** (check for ranges in different productions)\n3. **\"Seasons of Love\" - Rent** (can work for multiple parts)\n4. **\"Of Course\" - The Last Five Years**\n5. **\"Maybe This Time\" - Cabaret**\n\nThese songs provide a mix of styles and should allow for some fun and engaging performances. Remember to check the specific vocal ranges of each song, as keys can vary and you might find some songs easier to sing in different arrangements. Enjoy your karaoke session!",
